# Canonical read models

## Rule

When a repository has canonical read services, SQL views, selectors, serializers,
DTO builders, or API response mappers, all list/detail/timeline/export reads for
that resource must use the canonical path.

## Checklist

1. Identify the canonical read service or view before adding a new read path.
2. Do not duplicate complex joins or response-shape logic in routes/components.
3. New columns must be added to the canonical path first, then consumers.
4. Tests and mocks must reflect the canonical row/DTO shape.
5. Deploy-skew must be handled for recently added read fields.
6. Sort order and pagination must be consistent across list/detail/export.

## Pre-commit check

- [ ] No duplicate read-shape logic was introduced.
- [ ] Canonical read model was updated first.
- [ ] Consumers and tests use the same shape.
